x4freetext: Targets consisted of approximately 1 mg/cm2 thick
self supporting foils of greater than 98 % enrichment
in the isotope of interest. To allow ous detection of
scattered particles on both sides of the beam, the
targets mounted at 90 degr. to the beam direction for
the forward and the backward angle rements, and rotated
by 45 degr. for the intermediate angles.
Four silicon surface barrier detectors were
mounted on both sides of the beam line, 7.5 degr.
apart and 25 cm from the center of the chamber.
Measurements at the 175 degr. were done
A uniform error has been assumed for all
Where no error bars are shown the uncertainty is
smaller than the size of the experimental points.
The differential cross sections were derived directly
from the yields obtained in analyzing power
measurements. The absolute normalization was determined
by measuring Rutherford scattering for 4 MeV deuterons
at a number of angles below 60 degr. (lab).
The normalization of the 12 MeV data for 60Ni had to
